						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Nandi-pillar near the Hanumān temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>The purpose of this fragmentary and worn out inscription is not clear. It seems to record a grant of land in the presence of certain <hi rend="italic">Prabhugāvuṇḍus</hi> and others. The characters belong to about the <hi rend="bold">13th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
